reviews_data.review_text: Efficient store. I was able to get my iced coffe, relax and stay for an hour, reading. I enjoyed it.

The man who helped me was very rude. Not sure why because my daughter and I were the only customers there early that morning. He was just standing there looking at us when we walked up to the counter. I had to speak to him first, and he still didn't even say anything. So I just went ahead and told him what i wanted. After I ordered my coffee, we ended up standing to the side of the register just in case someone came in to order too. After he made my drink, he put my drink on the other side of the counter where people would usually pick up their drinks when their names were called if it was super busy. And he didn't even say anything. I was talking to my daughter during that time and didn't even realized he was finished with my drink then I finally made eye contact with him 2 minutes later, and he said oh your drink is over there and pointed where it was at. So I had to walk all the way to the other side to get my drink. I was so upset cause he could've just handed the drink to me cause we were the only ones there. No customers anywhere. I'm not sure if he did that because of my race, but he made me feel that way. I wouldn't be going back to this Starbucks. I'll take my money somewhere else since my daughter and my present were so disgusting to him to the point where he didn't want to serve us.

The Store Manager Matthew at 11510 Waverly Center Dr, Charlotte is extremely unprofessional and I want to report the below incident. On May 18, 2024, I used the mobile app to make my usual order a Royal English Breakfast Tea with splash of oat milk and 5 packs of Splenda.

After picking up my order, it was clearly wrong, which is an issue I've had about 5 times in the past few weeks to inform the manager of this issue. When I spoke to the manager Mathew about my issue he offered a free drink, which I politely declined and let him know my goal of the call was to let him know what could be done to have my tea made correctly through mobile ordering, because once I pick up my order I need to get to work on time, so it would be helpful for my daily routine. Matthew negatively responded and told me if his location keeps messing up my drink every time or every other time I should go to another location " he said I wouldn't come here I'd go somewhere else" where they don't mess up my drink, (how does that resolve the issue. either i'm being targeted bc it's a mobile order same name same order or your messing everyone's drink up and they not complaining) he went on to say I have an excellent staff and I'm watching them make my drinks. Sounds like to me neither Matthew or his staff do not have any attention to detail as there's no oat milk or sugar in my drink like the label says so. Clearly In the picture. I understand that mistakes happen and I am a very patient person, but this is not the type of customer service response that is effective or appreciated from a global public company.

So I spend almost $1,000 a month at this particular Starbucks, going 2 or sometimes even 3 times a day. I order the exact same drink every time for myself. I ask for it to be made a specific way but it's not like rocket science, it's a venti cup filled half way up with a tall white chocolate mocha and the other half with whip and a ton of caramel crunch topping which I get charged a little extra for. I have no problem paying whatever extra amount they think is appropriate for the extra crunch topping. Anyway, I've had to send my drink back several times to be remade correctly and I'll hear different members of the staff talking smack about me because I want my drink made right. I'm sorry but if I'm spending that kind of money somewhere I expect to get what I am paying for. So because I expect my drink and food to be made right and return it when it's not and because I have gotten frustrated when I've heard the staff making rude comments about me I have basically been told I'm not welcome there. Keep in mind when my drink is right I tip 2, 5, and sometimes even 10 dollars. I'm just saying, don't expect your money or loyalty to matter at this particular location.

i've been here multiple times and usually had friendly quick service.  However, on Wednesday (9/6) morning at 7:15am - on my way to work...I wanted a quick coffee.  I sat in the drive through line for over 15 min. I could see people walking in and out during the time I was just sitting there.  I couldn't back up because there were cars behind me.   When I finally got to the window I asked the lady what happened and she said they'd had lots of issues and that's why it took so long.  considering that people use the drive through so that it's quick...when you know your drive through is not moving perhaps it would be helpful to send someone out to alert customers.  Or even better, just make the coffee free for the people that were waiting over 15 min.  For the approx $5/customer it might have cost them it would have generated immense goodwill.  I know I will not be stopping at this Starbucks any more on my way to work.
